### 1. Understand JavaScript Fundamentals: 
React.js is built with JavaScript, so having a strong understanding of JavaScript fundamentals is crucial. Ensure you're comfortable with concepts like variables, functions, arrays, objects, and ES6 syntax.

### 2. Learn HTML and CSS: 
While not directly related to React.js, understanding HTML and CSS is essential for building user interfaces. Familiarise yourself with HTML elements, CSS styling, and responsive design principles.

### 3. Follow Online Tutorials and Courses: 
The best way to learn react js is utilise online tutorials and courses to supplement your learning. Platforms like [JustAcademy](https://www.justacademy.co/), They offer structured React.js courses with expert-led instruction, hands-on projects, and community support. With comprehensive resources and personalised guidance, JustAcademy ensures efficient learning and skill development, empowering individuals to excel in React.js development.

